Name: Lion
Description: Hunts large prey like zebras and antelope; apex predator in the savannah ecosystem.

Name: African Elephant
Description: Consumes grass, bark, and fruit; shapes the savannah by knocking down trees.

Name: Cheetah
Description: Fastest land animal; preys on gazelles and smaller ungulates.

Name: Secretary Bird
Description: Hunts snakes and insects on the ground; unique terrestrial bird of prey.

Name: Plains Zebra
Description: Feeds on grass and plays a role in shaping savannah vegetation.

Name: Scarlet Macaw
Description: Eats fruits, nuts, and seeds; important seed disperser in the rainforest.

Name: Jaguar
Description: Apex predator; hunts a variety of prey, including caimans and capybaras.

Name: Poison Dart Frog
Description: Feeds on insects; produces potent toxins for defense.

Name: Sloth
Description: Eats leaves high in trees; moves slowly to conserve energy.

Name: Green Anaconda
Description: Non-venomous constrictor that preys on large animals, including deer and fish.

Name: Fennec Fox
Description: Nocturnal; eats insects, rodents, and fruits; adapted to desert heat.

Name: Camel
Description: Stores fat in humps; consumes desert vegetation.

Name: Sidewinder Snake
Description: Venomous snake that preys on lizards and small mammals.

Name: Kangaroo Rat
Description: Consumes seeds; can survive without direct water intake.

Name: Desert Tortoise
Description: Eats desert plants and dig burrows to escape heat.

Name: Blue Whale
Description: Consumes krill; largest animal on Earth.

Name: Clownfish
Description: Forms symbiotic relationship with sea anemones.

Name: Sea Turtle
Description: Eats seagrass and jellyfish; important for marine ecosystems.

Name: Great White Shark
Description: Apex predator; hunts seals and large fish.

Name: Sea Otter
Description: Feeds on sea urchins and keeps kelp forests in balance.

Name: Hyena
Description: Scavenger and hunter; plays a key role in cleaning the ecosystem.

Name: Giraffe
Description: Eats leaves high in acacia trees; tallest land animal.

Name: Warthog
Description: Feeds on roots, berries, and small animals.

Name: Crowned Crane
Description: Eats insects, seeds, and small vertebrates.

Name: Termite
Description: Breaks down plant material and builds large mounds.

Name: Toucan
Description: Feeds on fruits; aids in seed dispersal.

Name: Capuchin Monkey
Description: Eats fruits, insects, and small animals; highly intelligent.

Name: Tapir
Description: Feeds on foliage and fruits in the dense forest.

Name: Harpy Eagle
Description: Preys on monkeys and sloths; apex predator of the canopy.

Name: Leafcutter Ant
Description: Cuts leaves to cultivate fungal gardens.

Name: Meerkat
Description: Feeds on insects, eggs, and plants; lives in social groups.

Name: Gila Monster
Description: Venomous lizard that preys on eggs and small mammals.

Name: Roadrunner
Description: Eats insects, lizards, and fruits; adapted to desert running.

Name: Scorpion
Description: Venomous arachnid that preys on insects and small animals.

Name: Horned Lizard
Description: Feeds on ants; can squirt blood from eyes as defense.

Name: Alligator
Description: Top predator in wetland ecosystems; preys on fish, birds, and mammals.

Name: Great Egret
Description: Hunts fish and amphibians in shallow waters.

Name: Muskrat
Description: Eats plants and small aquatic creatures; builds lodges in wetlands.

Name: Bullfrog
Description: Preys on insects, small fish, and other frogs.

Name: Red-winged Blackbird
Description: Feeds on seeds and insects; nests in wetland vegetation.

Name: Polar Bear
Description: Apex predator that preys on seals and other marine animals.

Name: Arctic Fox
Description: Feeds on small mammals, birds, and carrion.

Name: Emperor Penguin
Description: Feeds on fish and krill; breeds in extreme cold.

Name: Walrus
Description: Feeds on mollusks; uses tusks to haul itself out of water.

Name: Snowy Owl
Description: Preys on lemmings and other small mammals.

Name: Bison
Description: Feeds on grasses; keystone species of grassland ecosystems.

Name: Pronghorn Antelope
Description: Eats grass and sagebrush; fastest land mammal in North America.

Name: Burrowing Owl
Description: Hunts insects and small rodents; nests in burrows.

Name: Black-tailed Prairie Dog
Description: Eats grass and creates extensive burrow systems.

Name: Coyote
Description: Preys on small mammals and scavenges; highly adaptable.

Name: Sea Lion
Description: Feeds on fish and squid; lives along rocky coasts.

Name: Brown Pelican
Description: Dives to catch fish; nests on coastal cliffs.

Name: Horseshoe Crab
Description: Feeds on small invertebrates; crucial for medical research.

Name: Piping Plover
Description: Feeds on insects and crustaceans in sandy beaches.

Name: Blue Crab
Description: Feeds on detritus, plants, and small animals; key to coastal ecosystems.

Name: Red Fox
Description: Preys on rodents and birds; also eats fruits and insects.

Name: Woodpecker
Description: Feeds on insects and tree sap; drills into wood for food.

Name: Eastern Chipmunk
Description: Eats nuts, seeds, and insects; stores food in underground burrows.

Name: Raccoon
Description: Highly adaptable scavenger; eats fruits, small animals, and garbage.

Name: Barred Owl
Description: Nocturnal hunter that preys on rodents and small birds.

Name: Mudskipper
Description: Can breathe through its skin and lives between land and water.

Name: Saltwater Crocodile
Description: Apex predator of mangrove ecosystems; preys on fish and mammals.

Name: Mangrove Crab
Description: Feeds on mangrove leaves and small invertebrates.

Name: Roseate Spoonbill
Description: Wades through water to catch fish and crustaceans.

Name: Tree Climbing Crab
Description: Climbs mangroves to feed on leaves.

Name: Mountain Goat
Description: Feeds on grasses and shrubs; adapted to steep, rocky terrain.

Name: Snow Leopard
Description: Hunts mountain prey like ibex and sheep.

Name: Alpine Salamander
Description: Preys on small insects and worms.

Name: Golden Eagle
Description: Hunts mammals and birds in mountainous areas.

Name: Pika
Description: Eats alpine vegetation; stores food for winter.

Name: Clown Triggerfish
Description: Feeds on crustaceans and mollusks.

Name: Parrotfish
Description: Eats algae and dead coral; helps maintain reef health.

Name: Moray Eel
Description: Hides in crevices and preys on fish and invertebrates.

Name: Lionfish
Description: Venomous predator that hunts small fish.

Name: Blue Tang
Description: Eats algae; contributes to reef cleanliness.

Name: Blind Cave Fish
Description: Adapted to live in total darkness; feeds on detritus and small organisms.

Name: Bats
Description: Hunts insects using echolocation.

Name: Cave Salamander
Description: Feeds on cave-dwelling insects.

Name: Cave Cricket
Description: Consumes organic debris in caves.

Name: Olm
Description: Blind amphibian that preys on small aquatic invertebrates.

Name: Spider Monkey
Description: Eats fruits, leaves, and insects; lives in the canopy.

Name: Tree Frog
Description: Feeds on insects and uses suction pads to cling to leaves.

Name: Three-toed Sloth
Description: Slow-moving herbivore that spends most of its life in trees.

Name: Macaw
Description: Brightly colored parrot that feeds on seeds and fruits.

Name: California Quail
Description: Feeds on seeds, berries, and insects.

Name: Bobcat
Description: Hunts rabbits, rodents, and birds in scrubland areas.

Name: Black Bear
Description: Feeds on berries, insects, and small mammals.

Name: White-tailed Deer
Description: Feeds on forest vegetation, including leaves and twigs.

Name: Eastern Gray Squirrel
Description: Feeds on nuts, seeds, and tree bark.
